3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates APT/USDT funding rates hourly using a composite of spot price indices and perpetual mark prices. The DEX's off-chain matching engine processes funding calculations instantly, while Starknet settlement ensures secure rate exchanges. Cross-margin positions allow traders to optimize funding exposure across multiple Aptos-related positions simultaneously."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","APT","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT perpetuals exhibit distinct funding patterns due to Aptos ecosystem volatility and lower retail participation compared to major pairs. The hourly funding frequency on RabbitX creates more granular arbitrage windows, while zero gas costs eliminate the fee drag common in Ethereum-based perpetual platforms."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical APT Funding Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT funding rates on RabbitX typically range from -0.05% to 0.15% hourly during normal market conditions. The pair shows pronounced funding spikes during Aptos ecosystem announcements or major DeFi protocol launches on the network. Correlation analysis reveals APT funding often moves independently from Bitcoin and Ethereum, creating isolated arbitrage opportunities. Weekend periods frequently see funding compression as institutional participation decreases across Aptos markets."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"RabbitX Arbitrage Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Zero gas fees on RabbitX enable micro-arbitrage strategies that remain unprofitable on gas-heavy networks. The exchange's cross-margin system allows funding arbitrageurs to hedge APT exposure using correlated Layer 1 positions like ETH or SOL. Off-chain order matching provides sub-second execution for funding rate captures, crucial during high-volatility periods when rates shift rapidly. Position sizing can be adjusted hourly without gas concerns, optimizing capital efficiency for rate harvesting."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT's mid-tier volume creates slippage risks during large position entries, particularly when funding rates signal overcrowded trades. RabbitX's early-stage protocol status introduces smart contract and liquidity risks not present on established centralized exchanges. The limited pair selection restricts hedging options, requiring careful correlation analysis with available trading pairs. Funding rate reversals can be swift in smaller cap L1 tokens, demanding tight stop-loss protocols and position monitoring."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are APT funding rates updated on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX updates APT/USDT funding rates every hour, providing 24 settlement periods per day. This frequent update schedule creates more arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour funding cycles on traditional exchanges."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for APT funding arbitrage on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for APT perpetual futures. Combined with zero gas costs, total trading expenses remain significantly lower than Layer 1 alternatives for frequent funding rate strategies."},{"question":"Can I use cross-margin for APT funding rate trades?","answer":"Yes, RabbitX supports cross-margin trading for APT/USDT perpetuals. This allows you to use collateral from other positions to support funding rate strategies while maintaining hedged exposure across multiple assets."},{"question":"What's the typical APT funding rate range on RabbitX?","answer":"APT funding rates on RabbitX typically fluctuate between -0.1% to 0.2% hourly during standard market conditions. Extreme rates above 0.5% or below -0.3% usually indicate significant market imbalances and potential arbitrage opportunities."}]}]
